data.text:
The 2024 Paris Olympics is a prestigious sporting event where tennis players from across the world will compete to fulfill their Olympic dreams. Viewers can enjoy the action at the famous Stade Roland Garros stadium from July 27 to August 4. This will be the first Olympic event that will be played on a natural surface since the 1992 Barcelona Olympics.

The tennis event will feature 172 players participating in five events - men's and women's singles, men's and women's doubles, and mixed doubles. The tournament will be best of three sets and played in six rounds in the men's and women's singles categories. It will be played in five rounds in the doubles category and four rounds in the mixed doubles category.

Men's World No. 1 Jack Sinner will be making his Olympic debut, while this will be women's World No. 1 Iga Swiatek's second Olympic appearance after playing in the 2020 Tokyo Olympics. Two-time Olympic champion Rafael Nadal will team up with reigning French Open and Wimbledon winner Carlos Alcaraz. Other players to watch out for include American favorite Coco Gauff, back-to-back Grand Slam finalist Jasmine Paolini, and 2024 Wimbledon Champion in the women's category Barbora Krejcikova.
